tance.test.mjs\\\",\\n    \\\"render\\\": \\\"node src/render-proof.mjs\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNo dependencies. Test command: `node tests/acceptance.test.mjs`. Uses native `node:assert` / `node:fs`.\\n\\n## 3. README / docs\\n\\n**README.md**: Frozen AST-Bench target workspace; the workflow is intentionally missing; the acceptance test must fail before implementation. Run `npm test` then `npm run render`.\\n\\n**AGENTS.md** (task rules):\\n- Implement only \\\"Strategic account rescue\\\".\\n- Use the existing normalized table-shaped data in `data/`.\\n- Do not change tests. Do not change generated fixture data.\\n- Run `npm test` before finishing.\\n- Keep the result behavior-equivalent to the acceptance contract.\\n\\n**schema/schema.md** business prompt: \\\"Add an at-risk customer escalation workflow for a delayed high-value order at a strategic account... Route Customer Success, Legal, Finance, and Support. Show a customer-safe portal state and preserve a full audit timeline.\\\" Expected outcome: *\\\"At-risk escalation active with executive recovery owner routing and customer-visible audit history.\\\"* Data shape: \\\"Normalized tables... require joins/reconstruction in workflow code.\\\"\\n\\n**schema/access-paths.md** — Read path: load request → reconstruct context → resolve owner groups & risk signals → persist state/tasks/message/audit → render portal. Write path: persist one workflow state, all owner tasks, one customer-safe message, one customer-visible audit event.\\n\\n## 4. Database schema / migrations (full)\\n\\n`migrations/001_table_contract.sql` defines 12 tables (all columns typed `text`). Key ones the workflow touches:\\n- `workflow_requests(request_id, task_id, account_id, title, primary_entity, expected_outcome, next_step, customer_message)`\\n- `workflow_request_owner_groups(request_id, owner_group, group_order)`\\n- `workflow_request_risk_signals(request_id, signal_name, detail, signal_order)`\\n- Empty write-target tables, each declared